body:
Hello,

I found that a recursive function with `return` statement triggers an assertion failure in vvp.

Here is a test program (derived from `ivtest/ivltests/recursive_func.v`):
```systemverilog
module test();

function automatic [15:0] factorial;
  input [15:0] n;
  return (n > 1) ? factorial(n - 1) * n : n;
endfunction

wire [15:0] r4;

assign r4 = factorial(6);

initial begin
  #1;
  $display("factorial 6 = %0d", r4);
end

endmodule
```
Compiling with current git version (42de9e64) succeeds, but simulation fails:
```
$ iverilog -g2012 -Wall test.sv
$ ./a.out
vvp: vthread.cc:3763: void do_join(vthread_t, vthread_t): Assertion `child->parent == thr' failed.
Abort
```

